<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE083">
<l>unti mutalā muntuvaḷit tōṉṟit</l>
<l>talaiyiṉu miṭaṟṟiṉu neñciṉu nilaiip</l>
<l>pallu mitaḻu nāvu mūkku</l>
<l>maṇṇamu muḷappaṭa veṇmuṟai nilaiyā</l>
<l>ṉuṟuppuṟ ṟamaiya neṟippaṭa nāṭi</l>
<l>yellā veḻuttuñ colluṅ kālaip</l>
<l>piṟappi ṉākkam vēṟuvē ṟiyala</l>
<l>tiṟappaṭat teriyuṅ kāṭci yāṉa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It will be evident on careful observation</l>
<l>that all sounds when pronounced are produced in different ways</l>
<l>as the results of the modifications undergone</l>
<l>by the rising air<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">muntuvaḷi</foreign> ' air [in the body] ', ' breath '.</note> starting from the navel<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">unti.</foreign></note></l>
<l>and passing through the eight places in [its] course -</l>
<l>the head, and the throat, and the chest,<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">talai</foreign> ' head ' as resonator? Cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">śiras</foreign> in <foreign xml:lang="sa">Pāṇinīyaśikṣā</foreign> ; <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">miṭaṟu</foreign> ' throat ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">kaṇṭha</foreign> in <foreign xml:lang="sa">Pāṇinīyaś.</foreign> ; <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">neñcu</foreign> ' chest ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">uras</foreign> in the above-mentioned text.</note></l>
<l>the teeth, and the lips, and the tongue, and the nose,<note
              place="foot"><foreign
                xml:lang="ta">pal</foreign> ' teeth ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">dantāh</foreign> in the text mentioned above ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">itaḻ</foreign> ' lips ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">uṣṭhau</foreign> in <foreign xml:lang="sa">Pāṇinīyaś</foreign>., <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">nā</foreign> ' tongue ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">jihvāmūlam</foreign> in Pāṇini ; <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">mūkku</foreign> ' nose ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">nāsika</foreign> in Pāṇini.</note></l>
<l>and the palate.<note
              place="foot"><foreign
                xml:lang="ta">aṇṇam</foreign> ' palate ', cf. Skt. <foreign
                xml:lang="sa">tālu</foreign> in <foreign xml:lang="sa">Pāṇini.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
